# Sense to Respond - Cursor Rules

You are editing a spec-driven AI/harness project. Follow these rules strictly.

## Read first
Before code changes, read:
- docs/architecture.md
- docs/planning.md
- rules.md
- relevant docs/contracts/* if touched

## Core invariants
- Spec before code.
- IA = LLM + Harness.
- LLM never calculates numbers (metrics, deviations, DOI, financial impact).
- LLM CAN generate ETL scripts (rename, groupby, merge) but NOT metric scripts (ADR-0021).
- ETL scripts generated by LLM require human review before execution.
- Python/pandas tools calculate all metrics and financial values.
- On the PBI path (ADR-0025), metrics come from catalog DAX via MCP ExecuteQuery; do not use GenerateQuery in the batch report path; do not reimplement PBI measures in Python as the default fallback.
- Dual ingress: spreadsheet = DataShield; unified PBI = Dominion PBI + DAX catalog. Mondelez PBI catalog is post-PoC backlog (planning 1.7a).
- MVP uses sequential pipeline and state blackboard.
- No free natural-language conversation between agents in MVP.
- No MOE router, consensus, or Bridge execution unless spec is updated first.
- Human-in-the-loop is mandatory (via InterfaceHITL protocol, ADR-0022).
- Every HITL decision is saved as auditable JSON (ADR-0023).

## Change flow
1. Classify change: fix, refactor, feature, architecture, prompt, security, test, docs.
2. If architecture/prompt/security/state/tool contract changes: update docs/architecture.md first.
3. Use next unchecked item in docs/planning.md unless user explicitly requests otherwise.
4. Implement the smallest safe change.
5. Add/update tests when behavior changes.
6. Run at least: python main.py --modo nexus.
7. If pipeline behavior changed: update docs/sense_to_respond_modelagem.tex in the same session and recompile the PDF (pdflatex). Model only what is implemented; planned work goes under "Proximos Passos", never as an invariant. Do not mark planning.md [x] while the LaTeX is stale.
8. Update docs/planning.md only when acceptance criteria pass.
9. Update docs/agent.log.md at the end.

## Code rules
- Strict typing for public functions.
- Avoid Any in new public APIs.
- No silent exceptions.
- No real secrets or client data in code, logs, docs, tests.
- Tools must be deterministic and audited.
- LLM calls must use structured JSON, validation, retry, and safe fallback.

## Git (ver tambem git-human-commit.mdc)
- Agent may analyze diffs and advise what should go to the repo.
- Suggest commit message (story of the change) and copy-paste commands.
- Do NOT run `git commit` or `git push`; the human executes them in the terminal.

## Stop and ask
Ask before:
- changing state/tool/proposition contracts;
- adding new decision types;
- adding autonomous execution;
- modifying guardrails;
- removing human review;
- touching more than 5 code files;
- generating or executing ETL scripts in production;
- changing HITL protocol or InterfaceHITL implementations.